headline: PCAR Q1 Earnings Call: Tariff Uncertainty and Margin Pressure Shape Outlook
summary: Trucking company PACCAR (NASDAQ:PCAR) fell short of the market’s revenue expectations in Q1 CY2025, with sales falling 16% year on year to $6.91 billion. Its non-GAAP profit of $1.46 per share was 7.5% below analysts’ consensus estimates.
